sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:2006:sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:22:All five ArtistModes are exercised: `solitary`, `companion`, `working_ambience`, `evening_reflection`, `storm`. The smoke entry point is hardware-free, as required by the task spec. Documentation was updated in both `cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` and `cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to register `sampler_fx_mode_verify.py` in the landed-components table and inline the `EffectsBus.apply_mode` call site into the dispatch-flow description. The architecture test's `LANDED_COMPONENTS` tuple was extended to include the new verifier path.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:2008:sdp/verification/t-020@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:28:The smoke verifier follows the exact pattern of `sample_capture_verify.py` (hardware-free, deterministic, no live audio required). Test naming mirrors the `test_sampler_dispatch.py` style. `MODE_SEQUENCE` is derived from `tuple(FX_PRESETS_BY_MODE)` rather than hardcoded, so it stays in sync automatically if the preset table grows. The OSC recording stub (`_RecordingOSC`) in the verifier matches the in-test stub pattern.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:2029:sdp/verification/frac-0052-verify.md:49:- Test file structure matches existing `test_sampler_dispatch_depth.py` conventions: `_RecordingOSC`, `_Record` stubs, `_write_wav` helper, `_module()` import accessor.
sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0113_1777794485.log:2031:sdp/verification/frac-0052-verify.md:54:No security concerns. Implementation is stdlib-only (no network I/O, no subprocess calls, no file writes, no credentials). `temp_sampler_dispatch.py` is a scratch diagnostic module with no HTTP surface. OSC messages pass through caller-supplied `_OSCSender` — no injection vectors introduced. No new dependencies added to `pyproject.toml`.
